  "doc_id": "6396",
  "text": "In the entire cohort of LA eyes, VEP amplitudes were reduced and ITs were delayed significantly (P < 0.01) when we used the large (60 0 ) and small (15 0 ) checks stimulations. These results were expected due to the variable degree of optic nerve damage and optic nerve fibers' degeneration. However, our findings are cross-sectional in nature and, the sequence of pathologic events proposed by Barboni et al. [CITATION_1] is not highlighted by our study. These investigators reported that the smaller-caliber fibers of the papillomacular bundle are selectively damaged in the initial phase of the acute disease and later extend to the rest of the axons of the optic nerve when the optic atrophy occurs. Consistent with this hypothesis, Carelli et al. [CITATION_2] suggested that the papillomacular bundle is the main target in the early stages of the degenerative process of LHON.",
